  "instructions": [
    "In a small bowl, mix tahini, soy sauce, sesame oil, ginger paste, red pepper flakes, and garlic paste. Gradually add water while whisking continuously to achieve a smooth consistency.",
    "Heat a wok or large skillet over medium-high heat. Add scallions and cooked for 1 minute until softened.",
    "Add fermented black beans and continue cooking for another minute until fragrant.",
    "Pour in the tahini mixture, and stir-fry for an additional 2 minutes until the sauce thickens slightly.",
    "Serve hot as a side dish or over rice."
